JOHANNESBURG - Pimville residents in Soweto have taken to the streets on Monday morning. It's unclear what they are unhappy about, however, they have blocked roads causing traffic disruptions. The JMPD has advised motorists to use alternative routes. "Motorists are advised to exercise caution they can use Mogaji  street or Mokoena street and  Mosaka street as alternative routes," the JMPD said. In Pimville theres a report of protests on Chris Hani Road near Maponya Mall  rather use Modjadji Street #JHBTraffic  In Pimville Chris Hani Road is closed off to traffic near Maponya Mall due to protests  rather use Modjadji Street #JHBTraffic 